Gandhi Bilel Djuna (French pronunciation: ​[ɡɑ̃di bilɛl dʒuna]; born 6 May 1986), better known by his stage name Maître Gims and more recently just Gims (, GHIMSS; French: [mɛtʁə ɡims]) (sometimes stylized as GIMS), is a Congolese-French singer-songwriter and rapper.
He grew up in France and currently lives in France and Morocco.
He is a former member of the hip hop group Sexion d'Assaut and released his first major album, Subliminal in 2013.
